desktop\/modal\/help.cronSyntaxe.php.Une fois par an à 5h10 le 18 Février: Once a year at 5:10 a.m. on February 18
desktop\/modal\/help.cronSyntaxe.php.Une fois par mois à 18:14 le second jour: Once a month at 6:14 p.m. on the second day of the month
desktop\/modal\/help.cronSyntaxe.php.Une fois par semaine le mardi à 12:00: Once a week on Tuesday at 12:00
desktop\/modal\/help.cronSyntaxe.php.Le premier mardi du mois à 15h00: The first Tuesday of the month at 3:00 p.m.
desktop\/modal\/help.cronSyntaxe.php.Support pour chaque caractère spécial dé: Support for each special character depends on specific cron distributions and versions
desktop\/modal\/help.cronSyntaxe.php.L'astérisque indique que l'expression cr: The asterisk indicates that the expression cron matches all the values in the field. For example, using an asterisk in the 4th field (month) indicates all months of the year.
desktop\/modal\/help.cronSyntaxe.php.Les barres obliques décrivent l'incrémen: The slashes describe the range increment. For example 3-59 / 15 in the 1st field (minutes) indicates the third minute of the hour and every 15 minutes thereafter. The "* / ..." form is equivalent to the "first-last / ..." form, that is, an increase over the widest possible range of the field.
desktop\/modal\/help.cronSyntaxe.php.Pourcent (%) dans la commande, à moins q: Percent (%) in the command, unless escaped by a backslash (\), is changed to newline characters, and all data after the first% is sent to the command as standard input.
desktop\/modal\/help.cronSyntaxe.php.Les virgules sont utilisées pour séparer: Commas are used to separate items from a list. For example, using "MON, WED, FRI" in the 5th field (day of the week) means Mondays, Wednesdays and Fridays.
desktop\/modal\/help.cronSyntaxe.php.Tirets définissent les plages. Par exemp: Dashes define the ranges. For example, 2000-2010 indicates each year between 2000 and 2010 inclusive.
desktop\/modal\/help.cronSyntaxe.php.L' signifie \"dernier\". Lorsqu'il est u: L means "last". When used in the day of the week field, it allows you to specify constructs such as "last Friday" ("5L1") for a given month. In the day of month field, it specifies the last day of the month.
desktop\/modal\/help.cronSyntaxe.php.Le caractère «W» est autorisé pour le ch: The character “W” is authorized for the day of the month field. This character is used to specify the day of the week (Monday-Friday) closest to the given day. For example, if you were to specify "15W" as the value for the day of month field, the meaning is: "the week closest to the 15th of the month." So if the 15th is a Saturday, the trigger lights on Friday 14. If the 15th is a Sunday, the trigger lights Monday on the 16. If the 15th is a Tuesday, it triggers on Tuesday 15. However, if you specify "1W" as the value for the day of the month, and the 1st is a Saturday, the Monday trip lights the 3rd, as it does not "jump" on the day limit of a month. The character "W" can be defined only when the month day is a day , not a range or list of days.
desktop\/modal\/help.cronSyntaxe.php.«#» Est autorisé pour le champ du jour d: "#" Is allowed for the day of the week field, and must be followed by a number between one and five. It allows you to specify constructions such as "the second Friday" of a given month.
desktop\/modal\/help.cronSyntaxe.php.Remarque: Point d'interrogation est un c: Note: Question mark is an atypical character and only exists in some cron implementations. It is used in place of '*' to leave either blank day of the month or day of the week.
